The paper proposes a variant of Graph Neural Networks (GNNs) for representation learning, specifically focusing on the use of attention mechanisms in the spectral domain of graphs. This work is closely related to the fields of machine learning, artificial intelligence, computer vision, network analysis, and signal processing. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper deals with network analysis and signal processing, which are covered by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SI (Signal Processing).
